 surname and shortened it to 羅 during the Northern Wei dynasty (386–534  AD ). (iv) from the name of one of the seven families from the Bandun Man, an ethnic group residing in ancient southwestern China (located mainly in present-day Sichuan province)."]}]},{"name":"Mare","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Americo, Cesareo, Fernando, Ines, Javier, Jose, Marcos.  Portuguese Henrique.  Italian Antonio, Gino, Olindo, Silvio, Vito.  Dutch Andries.","Italian: topographic name for someone living by the sea, from <i>mare</i> ‘sea’.","English: variant of   Mear  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Marucci","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Rocco, Antonio, Silvio, Angelo, Carmela, Domenic, Donato, Egidio, Guido, Licinio, Lorenzo, Luciano.","Italian: patronymic or plural form of the personal name <i>Maruccio</i>, a pet form of   Mare   or   Mari  ."]},{"name":"Marelli","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Rocco, Giuseppe, Angelo, Dante.","Italian:","patronymic or plural form of a diminutive of   Mare  ."]},{"name":"Mear","meanings":["Mear, a field; also from mear or mearh, a horse","Anglo-Saxon: Mere, lake, pool, sea"]}]},{"name":"Isabella","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of   Isabel  , which has been popular in England since the 18th century and has recently become the preferred form of the name."],"variants":[{"name":"Isobella","meanings":["form of   Isabel  , which has been popular in England since the 18th century and has recently become the preferred form of the name."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705189,"age":20,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"htt